  "prompt": "Why isn't hockey the national game of India?",
  "response": "Hockey is actually considered the national sport of India, despite not being the most popular sport in the country. Some key points about hockey in India:\n\n1. Historical success: India has been extremely successful in field hockey, winning multiple Olympic gold medals between 1928 and 1956.\n\n2. Official status: It was formally declared the national sport in 1926 during the British colonial period.\n\n3. Current popularity: Cricket has overshadowed hockey in terms of popularity and commercial success in recent decades.\n\n4. Decline in performance: India's hockey team has not maintained its earlier dominance in international competitions.\n\n5. Lack of infrastructure and investment: Compared to cricket, hockey receives less funding and support at grassroots levels.\n\nDespite being the official national sport, cricket has become the most watched and played sport in India, which has somewhat diminished hockey's prominence.",
